<build_gate_finding verbatim="true">

FINDING bg-004 (HIGH, rule correctness.spec-compliance):
POST /webhook crashes with an uncaught TypeError -> Express default 500 handler -> HTML stack trace leaked to the client, for ANY request whose Content-Type does not match express.json()'s type-matcher (missing Content-Type header entirely, or a non-JSON Content-Type such as text/plain), regardless of what the body bytes actually are. Root cause: express.json({verify}) only invokes the verify callback (which sets req.rawBody) when body-parser's internal type-matcher recognizes the Content-Type as JSON; when it doesn't match (or is absent), body-parser skips parsing/verify entirely and calls next() with no error, so req.rawBody stays undefined. Execution then reaches the /webhook route handler, which calls hasValidSignature(req), which unconditionally does crypto.createHmac('sha256', webhookSecret).update(req.rawBody) -- Hmac.update(undefined) throws TypeError. This throw is forwarded to Express's default error handler (it does not match the SyntaxError/entity.parse.failed guard), which emits an HTML 500 page with a stack trace instead of any JSON error shape. Reproduced live: (1) Content-Type: text/plain + well-formed JSON body + no signature -> 500 HTML crash. (2) same but WITH a validly-computed signature over the raw bytes -> still 500 HTML crash (a legitimately signed request never gets evaluated). (3) no Content-Type header + empty body -> 500 HTML crash. Control: Content-Type: application/json + empty body (with or without matching signature over empty string) correctly returns 401/400 JSON, because express.json() DOES invoke verify() for that Content-Type (with a zero-length Buffer), so req.rawBody is defined.
FIX HINT (from BUILD_GATE, not binding): "Guard hasValidSignature against a missing/undefined req.rawBody by treating it as an invalid signature rather than passing it to Hmac.update: e.g. add `if (!req.rawBody) return false;` as the first line of the function. This reuses the existing 401 invalid_signature response path in both call sites (the /webhook route handler and the JSON-parse error middleware) with no new branch, response shape, or flag. Add a regression test posting to /webhook with a non-JSON (or absent) Content-Type header and asserting 401."

</build_gate_finding>

<task>
Fix bg-004 exactly per the fix hint: guard `hasValidSignature(req)` so a missing/undefined `req.rawBody` returns `false` (invalid signature) instead of throwing. This is a one-line guard reusing the existing 401 path — do not add a new response shape, new branch, or new error type. Add one regression test: POST /webhook with a Content-Type that is not `application/json` (e.g. `text/plain`) and a well-formed JSON body, asserting the response is `401 { error: 'invalid_signature' }` (not a crash, not any other status).

Also double-check there is no third sibling of this same failure class you can find by inspecting every other place `req.rawBody` or `req.body` is read in the `/webhook` handler and the error middleware — if you find one, fix it too and say so explicitly in your reply. If you don't find one, say so explicitly too.
</task>

